## Code conventions

- TypeScript strict mode (`"strict": true`) — no implicit `any`, no unchecked indexing
- Prefer `readonly` properties on value objects and domain interfaces
- Use discriminated unions to model exhaustive domain states
- `interface` for domain contracts and ports; `type` aliases for unions and utility types
- `async`/`await` for all asynchronous code — avoid raw Promise chains
- No `any` — use `unknown` for truly unknown input and narrow explicitly
- ESLint enforces style; run `npm run lint:fix` before committing
- Every exported function and interface has a JSDoc comment
- No `process.exit()` in library code — only in the application entry point
